# Project Specification - Goal Timer App (v1.0)

## Project Purpose

Create a mobile app that helps users take action towards becoming their ideal self by focusing on goals and building habits. The app targets people who often waste time on entertainment or procrastination and want to reclaim that time to work on important personal goals.

---

## Target Users

- Age: Primarily up to 20s (students, young professionals)
- Gender: Both male and female
- Characteristics:
  - Easily distracted by SNS, short videos, games
  - Have a vague feeling of "I should do this" but fail to take action
  - Lose track of their long-term goals due to daily distractions

---

## Key User Scenarios

- Start timer when allocating time to work on a goal
- Review progress and streak history to maintain motivation

---

## Differentiators

- "Negative Avoidance" input: User defines what will happen if they don't work on the goal
- Pomodoro Timer Mode (paid feature)
- Duolingo-inspired habit reinforcement (reminders, streaks, gamification)
- Making the act of continuing feel enjoyable and rewarding

---

## Design & UI Guidelines

### Design System

- Base color: White (clean, simple background)
- Main color: #3B82F6 (blue - focus, positive energy)
- Accent colors: Grays for structure, Gold for reward moments
- Font: Sans-serif (SF Pro, Roboto, platform native)

### UI Pattern

- Minimal & native-feeling
- Generous spacing for stress-free operation
- One-purpose-per-screen principle
- Large and easy-to-tap buttons

### UX Priorities

- 1️⃣ Ease of use
- 2️⃣ Motivation to continue
- 3️⃣ Visual aesthetics

### Visual Inspiration

- Duolingo
- Streaks
- Forest
- Apple Reminders

### Worldview Tagline

> "Don’t waste your youth. A few minutes every day can change your future."

---

## Technical & Implementation Guidelines

### Platform
- iOS & Android (cross-platform)

### Development Approach

- Flutter

### Authentication

- Google Login
- Apple Login (iOS only)
- Email & Password login

#### Platform-specific login UI:
- Android: Google, Email & Password
- iOS: Google, Apple, Email & Password

### Data Storage

- Cloud: Supabase
- Local: SQLite (for offline use)

### External Services

- Crashlytics (crash monitoring)
- Google Analytics (behavior analysis)
- RevenueCat (subscription management)

### Notifications

- Local push notifications
- Daily reminder: 2 hours & 30 minutes before the new day starts (based on device time)

### Subscription

- Pomodoro Timer behind paid plan
- Other paid features under consideration post-MVP

---

## MVP Scope (v1.0)

### Core Features

- User registration (Apple, Google, Email & Password)
- Goal management (create, edit, delete, multiple goals)
- Timer (simple count-up timer, pause/resume)
- Progress tracking (daily records, streak display, achievement rate)
- Negative Avoidance input during goal creation
- Local notifications for reminders
- SQLite local persistence
- Crashlytics & Analytics integration

### Post-MVP Candidates

- Pomodoro Timer (paid)
- Badges, gamification rewards
- Advanced analytics (weekly/monthly graphs)
- Subscription plan expansion
- Device sync via Supabase

---

## Development Process

- MVP phase: Flexible to adjust requirements during development
- Post-MVP phase: Requirements freeze and stability focus

---

